President Biden delivered a speech in Durham, North Carolina, addressing the recent shooting in Nashville and calling for action to stop gun violence. He expressed his condolences for the victims and emphasized the need to pass the assault weapons ban to prevent such tragedies. The President also highlighted the importance of investing in America and rebuilding the economy. He discussed the significant investments made in manufacturing, infrastructure, and clean energy, including the largest investment in manufacturing in North Carolina's history. President Biden emphasized the importance of bringing the supply chain back to America and creating good-paying jobs for American workers. He also mentioned partnerships with community colleges and HBCUs to train workers and build pipelines for jobs in various sectors. The President stressed the need to support American manufacturing and innovation and not let extreme MAGA Republicans undo the progress made. He concluded his speech by expressing his optimism about the future of the country and the potential of the United States when acting together.